## Signing into the Epic Launcher

(#Bookmark3)

After the set-up program installs the Epic Games Launcher on your machine, use your Epic Game account credentials to login.

![](EpicSignIn.png)

## Installing Unreal Engine

(#Bookmark4)

Now that you've signed into the Epic Games Launcher, you're ready to install UE4.

[REGION:warning]
[REGION:largetitle]
Space Requirements
[/REGION]
Unreal Engine uses approximately eight gigabytes of disk space for every version of the engine that is installed on a machine. Make sure you have plenty of disk space prior to installing UE4.
[/REGION]

1.	Click the **Unreal Engine** tab inside the Epic Games Launcher Loading Screen.

	![](LauncherLoadScreen.png)

1.	Click the **Install Engine** button to download and install the latest version of Unreal Engine.

	![](InstallEngine.png)

1.	Read our [Unreal Engine End User License Agreement](https://www.unrealengine.com/eula) (EULA) prior to clicking the **Accept** button.

	![](AcceptEULALauncher.png)

1.	Depending on your system specifications, downloading and installing Unreal Engine will take between 10-40 minutes.
	
	![](DownloadingEngine.png)

	_Example progress indicator (pictured above)._

## Launching Unreal Engine

(#Bookmark5)

After the Epic Games Launcher successfully downloads and installs Unreal Engine, you're ready to click the **Launch** button.

![](LaunchUE4.png)

Congratulations! You've learned how to:

&#x2713;	[Create an Epic Games account _(if you didn't already have one)_](#Bookmark1)  
